raw_text:
Endlich. Es ist vollbracht.

Ich sah mich nach St.Peter , während ich fürchtete das Urteil Ich wusste kommen würde meinen Weg . Das Licht begann , sich zurückzuziehen , wie meine Augen an das Licht gewöhnt und es tat Ich war entsetzt von meiner Umgebung.

Keine Pearly Gates . Nein überhaupt brennenden Flammen . Nur mein Bett im Dachboden meiner Mutter. Was ist passiert?

Während ich gefürchtet Tod und das folgende Schicksal , dass ich wusste mich erwartete ich konnte nicht belasten die Schuld nicht mehr. Es dauerte meine Jahre , den Mut zu tun, was ich wusste, dass ich gewinnen , aber ich werde dieses Mal nicht doddle . Noch umklammert meinen Walther Ich zog schnell den Lauf meiner Schläfe und ließ meine Scham ausfließen .

Endlich. Es ist vollbracht.

有一种青春叫宿舍
 【女生版】
 有各自的专属昵称
 每天被闹钟吵醒，
 所有人依然雷打不动，
 定闹钟的x位就是不关它，
 为的是呼唤三位大神起床.

"Yeah, yeah I get it, just shuddup down there. It's not like that'll get me any food anyway."

I mumbled in exasperation as my ears perked up to the sound of my stomach growling loudly. Usually, I had gotten by each day, sifting through dumpsters or deftly stealing dog food from bowls that their owners had lain out but today, I wasn't quite as lucky. Sure, it wasn't exactly dignified but a year spent squatting in god-forsaken corners of the streets and eating half-eaten meals that barely resembled food taught me one thing; Dignity was overrated.

Well that's the servers working finally we have enough power to get them working again.

Day 1 It's fascinating all human knowledge and ignorance given equal weight in this new medium.

Day 2 Our social scientist is having a field day with all the social media people seem to spend all their time documenting having a good time instead of just having fun.

I entered the room, and past a massive flame of a cake I saw a man celebrating his 731st birthday-yet somehow he looked even older than that. I snickered to myself at the number of candles on the cake and wondered if someone had actually counted out 731 candles or if they had to settle for fewer due to safety reasons. Maybe he had doubled his lifespan last year from a birthday cake mishap.

He staggered forward with pained movements as his ragged breath fell from his lips and sunk into the stillness of the room before him. His beady eyes locked the men before him, all clad in pure white; but covered in crimson stains. They all bore no visible wounds on their bodies, and as they stepped closer to the dishevelled man before them, a faint light filled the air and illuminated him for all he was.

The tallest of the group spoke in a voice that seemed grand and menacing, but his throat seemed to crack with every second word.
